Name: ATN/NO-8592-RG
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: The objective of the Program is to contribute to current processes that seek to increase the number and effectiveness of women in positions of leadership in civic and public life in Latin America.

Name: ATN/FF-8337-RS
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: The objective of this project is to document and disseminate the impact of various efforts by donor agencies on domestic violence interventions in the Caribbean region. In particular, this TC will fund surveys and analysis of the data to gauge the impact of the donor-financed trainings on different targetted groups (the police, trainers and victims) and the general public with a view to informing Bank's future support in this sector.

Name: ATN/FC-8353-RS
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: The long-term objective is the development of national and regional strategies for a competitive transition of the Central American coffee Sector. The short term objective is to support coffee producers with the income diversification process by improving their access to information and assistance regarding alternative products and markets.

Name: 1254/OP-NI
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: The general objective is to improve Nicaragua's competitiveness through reduced transport costs and increased production and trade. The specific objective is the integration of the project's influence zone to the Nicaraguan economy and consolidation if highway integration with Costa Rica and the other countries in the Mesoamerican region.

Name: ATN/CP-4077-BH
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: DEVELOP A ROAD NETWORK PLAN FOR NEW PROVIDENCE ISLAND FOR THE NEXT TEN YEARS AND THE ASSESSMENT OF THE TECHNICAL AND ECONOMIC FEASIBILITY OF HIGH PRIORITY INVESTMENT PROJECTS AND-OR TRAFFIC MANAGEMENT MEASURES.

Name: ATN/SC-4127-NI
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: TO IMPROVE HEALTH SERVICES IN NICARAGUA INCLUDING INSTITUTIONAL STRENGTHENING FOR THE MINISTRY OF HEALTH AND FEASIBILITY STUDIES FOR INVESTMENT PROJECTS.

Name: ATN/SD-4335-NI
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: THIS PROJECT IS DESIGNED TO STRENGTHEN GOVERNMENT POLICY FORMULATION WITH RESPECT TO THE SMALL AND MICROENTERPRISE SECTOR IN NICARAGUA. THE PROJECT WILL SUPPLY SPECIALIZED TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE IN ORDER TO SUPPORT THE RESEARCH AND INFORMATION GATHERING ABILITIES OF THE SMALL AND MICROENTERPRISE DIVISION OF THE MINISTRY OF ECONOMY AND DEVELOPMENT.

Name: ATN/SD-4093-UR
PSR_Executing_Agency_Text__c: ESCUELA DE LECHERIA DE COLONIA SUIZA
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: THE PROGRAM INTENDS TO STRENGTHEN THE ACADEMIC LEVEL OF THE DAIRY SCHOOL THROUGH AN ORGANIZATIONAL REFORM AND A FINANCIAL RESTRUCTURING SO AS TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF THE EDUCATIONAL PROGRAM AND REACH A STATUS AS AN ENTITY WITH FINANCIAL SELF-SUFFICIENCY.

Name: ATN/EC-4239-ME
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: THE OBJECTIVE IS TO ASSESS THE LEGAL CONDITIONS, INSTITUTIONAL MECHANISMS AND FLOWS OF RESOURCES THAT DETERMINE THE RELATIONS BETWEEN DIFFERENT LEVELS OF GOVERNMENT IN MEXICO. THIS T.C. WILL FIELD THREE INTERNATIONAL EXPERTS TO SUPPORT THE PREPARATION OF THE BANK'S MUNICIPAL DEVELOPMENT PROGRAM.

Name: ATN/SC-4609-PN
ORP_ProjectObjective__c: TO ASSIST THE GOVERNMENT OF PANAMA IN THE FORMULATION OF A MINING MASTER PLAN, THROUGH THE FINANCING OF TECHNICAL EXPERTISE IN THE FOLLOWING AREAS; LEGAL, INSTITUTIONAL, GEOLOGICAL, ECONOMIC, SOCIAL, CREDIT, FINANCING, ENVIRONMENT AND PROMOTION. THE OBJECTIVE OF THE MASTER PLAN IS TO REVIEW THE FACTORS THAT AFFECT THE MINING SECTOR IN PANAMA AND TO PREPARE A DOCUMENT WITH A STRATEGY TO DEVELOP THE SECTOR WITH AN INTEGRAL AND LONG TERM PERSPECTIVE.
